---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
const lastUpdated = '4 May 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Acceptable Use · Tamazia"
  description="Acceptable use of Tamazia services and the tamazia.co.uk website."
  canonical="https://tamazia.co.uk/acceptable-use/"
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <article class="legal-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">ACCEPTABLE USE</p>
      <p class="entity-disclosure"><em>Operated by Tamazia Ltd, an Indian private limited company with registered office in Mumbai, Maharashtra. Data Controller contact: dpo@tamazia.co.uk.</em></p>
      <h1>Acceptable use of Tamazia services</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {lastUpdated}.</p>

      <p>This policy supplements our <a href="/terms/">Terms of Service</a> and applies to anyone using the tamazia.co.uk website, our forms, our published content, or any service Tamazia delivers under engagement.</p>

      <h2>What you must not do</h2>
      <p>You must not use Tamazia services to send unsolicited bulk communications, distribute malware, infringe intellectual property rights of third parties, attempt to gain unauthorised access to systems, automate scraping at rates that disrupt our infrastructure, or impersonate any person or entity. You must not submit content that is unlawful, defamatory, obscene, or which incites violence.</p>

      <h2>Use of forms</h2>
      <p>The contact, briefings, and audit forms on tamazia.co.uk are intended for genuine commercial enquiries. Repeated submissions of fictitious or test data are blocked at the Cloudflare edge. Automated submissions without a human present are rejected by our bot defences.</p>

      <h2>Use of published content</h2>
      <p>Articles, case studies, and other content on tamazia.co.uk are published for the personal and professional reading of visitors. They may be linked to and quoted in passing under fair-dealing principles. They may not be republished in full, used to train artificial intelligence models, or reproduced in any service Tamazia would consider competing without prior written permission. Our /robots.txt records the relevant opt-outs.</p>

      <h2>Enforcement</h2>
      <p>Breaches may result in immediate revocation of service access, blocking at the network level, removal of content, and where the breach is material we may pursue injunctive relief or damages. We notify the relevant law-enforcement authority where conduct constitutes a criminal offence.</p>

      <h2>Reporting abuse</h2>
      <p>If you observe behaviour that breaches this policy, write to founder@tamazia.co.uk.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { background: var(--ivory); color: var(--oxblood-ink); padding: 88px 24px 120px; }
  .legal-inner { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .eyebrow { font-family: var(--ff-sans); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--oxblood); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .legal h1 { font-family: var(--ff-display); font-weight: 500; font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 52px); margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .updated { font-family: var(--ff-sans); font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .legal h2 { font-family: var(--ff-display); font-weight: 500; font-size: 24px; margin: 36px 0 12px; }
  .legal p { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .legal a { color: var(--oxblood); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold-soft); }
</style>
